WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:18.400
Mystery in San Francisco by Gina D. V. Clement Copyright, Black Cat Publishing.

00:31.000 --> 00:34.000
Introduction

00:34.000 --> 00:40.000
The story you are going to read takes place in San Francisco, California.

00:40.000 --> 00:44.000
San Francisco is a beautiful city on the Pacific Ocean.

00:44.000 --> 00:47.000
It is on a peninsula.

00:47.000 --> 00:51.000
San Francisco is on the San Andreas fault line.

00:51.000 --> 00:56.000
This means that sometimes there are earthquakes in San Francisco.

00:56.000 --> 01:01.000
A big earthquake in 1906 almost destroyed the city.

01:01.000 --> 01:06.000
The last serious earthquake was in 1989.

01:06.000 --> 01:11.000
It doesn't rain much and it is often foggy.

01:11.000 --> 01:16.000
You can see the fog arrive under the Golden Gate Bridge in the late afternoon.

01:16.000 --> 01:21.000
It stays all night and then it leaves late in the morning.

01:21.000 --> 01:24.000
At night you can hear fog horns.

01:25.000 --> 01:30.000
They warn ships on the ocean about dangerous weather conditions.

01:30.000 --> 01:34.000
The city has beautiful scenery because there are many hills,

01:34.000 --> 01:39.000
a lot of vegetation and attractive buildings.

01:41.000 --> 01:44.000
The North Beach Neighborhood

01:44.000 --> 01:48.000
North Beach is a traditionally Italian neighborhood

01:48.000 --> 01:52.000
with Italian food shops, cafes and restaurants.

01:52.000 --> 01:57.000
North Beach was one of the first settlements because it was near the bay.

01:57.000 --> 02:01.000
In the 1950s, many of the beach generation,

02:01.000 --> 02:06.000
a group of artists, writers and poets lived in North Beach.

02:06.000 --> 02:11.000
City Lights Bookstore was the center for these writers and poets.

02:11.000 --> 02:15.000
Today, you can still visit this bookstore.

02:15.000 --> 02:19.000
During the Gold Rush, Telegraph Hill was very important

02:19.000 --> 02:22.000
because it had a view of the bay.

02:22.000 --> 02:27.000
People on Telegraph Hill looked for sailing ships on the bay.

02:27.000 --> 02:33.000
When a sailing ship arrived, a messenger from Telegraph Hill went to tell the people.

02:33.000 --> 02:36.000
Today, there is a big tower on the hill.

02:36.000 --> 02:39.000
It is called Coit Tower.

02:39.000 --> 02:47.000
A woman called Lily Hitchcock Coit built it in honor of the firefighters of San Francisco.

02:47.000 --> 02:53.000
Washington Square is a lovely park and meeting place for the people of North Beach.

02:53.000 --> 02:58.000
Often, there are arts festivals in the Square.

03:06.000 --> 03:09.000
Chapter 1, Washington Square

03:10.000 --> 03:22.000
Jim Riley was 14 years old and he lived in the beautiful city of San Francisco in California.

03:22.000 --> 03:25.000
He was short, thin and wore glasses.

03:25.000 --> 03:28.000
He had brown hair and blue eyes.

03:28.000 --> 03:34.000
His mother died when he was 6 years old and his father lived in another city.

03:34.000 --> 03:36.000
Jim lived with his grandfather.

03:37.000 --> 03:41.000
This was his first year in high school and he liked it a lot.

03:41.000 --> 03:44.000
His favorite subject was science.

03:44.000 --> 03:49.000
On weekends, he had a part-time job at a supermarket to make extra pocket money.

03:49.000 --> 03:54.000
Jim's home was on Telegraph Hill near San Francisco Bay.

03:54.000 --> 03:59.000
From his living room, he could see the Golden Gate Bridge and the bay.

03:59.000 --> 04:02.000
Every morning, he walked down Telegraph Hill.

04:03.000 --> 04:06.000
He met his friends at the bus stop at Washington Square.

04:06.000 --> 04:10.000
They went to high school together.

04:10.000 --> 04:17.000
Washington Square was a historical landmark and the people of San Francisco loved to go there.

04:17.000 --> 04:20.000
It was a lovely park for children and adults.

04:20.000 --> 04:23.000
It was a small playground for children.

04:23.000 --> 04:27.000
It was also a place for the people of the North Beach neighborhood to meet.

04:27.000 --> 04:32.000
There were restaurants, cafes and nice shops around Washington Square.

04:32.000 --> 04:35.000
Often there were music and arts festivals.

04:35.000 --> 04:40.000
Normally, Washington Square had green grass and beautiful flowers.

04:40.000 --> 04:48.000
But there was no rain for a long time and the grass was dry and yellow and the flowers were dead.

04:49.000 --> 04:50.000
Hi, Jim.

04:50.000 --> 04:51.000
Said Brian.

04:51.000 --> 04:54.000
Brian Wilson was Jim's best friend.

04:54.000 --> 04:56.000
He was 14, too.

04:56.000 --> 05:00.000
He was a tall boy with blonde curly hair and green eyes.

05:00.000 --> 05:03.000
He played basketball on the high school team.

05:03.000 --> 05:07.000
His parents had a grocery store and he helped them on weekends.

05:07.000 --> 05:09.000
Hi, Brian.

05:09.000 --> 05:11.000
Did you finish your English homework?

05:11.000 --> 05:12.000
Said Jim.

05:12.000 --> 05:14.000
Yes, I did.

05:14.000 --> 05:16.000
But Shakespeare wasn't easy.

05:16.000 --> 05:18.000
Look, there's Susan.

05:18.000 --> 05:19.000
Said Brian.

05:19.000 --> 05:20.000
Hi, guys.

05:20.000 --> 05:22.000
Said Susan.

05:22.000 --> 05:25.000
Susan Hardy was a pretty African-American girl.

05:25.000 --> 05:28.000
She was a good friend of both boys.

05:28.000 --> 05:30.000
She was also a very good student.

05:30.000 --> 05:36.000
She had a part-time job as a babysitter for the children of her neighbors, the Moreno family.

05:36.000 --> 05:39.000
Her brother, Tom, was 20 years old.

05:39.000 --> 05:45.000
He was a biology student at San Francisco University and played on the University football team.

05:45.000 --> 05:48.000
Are you ready for the math test?

05:48.000 --> 05:49.000
Ask Susan.

05:49.000 --> 05:53.000
I studied all afternoon yesterday, but I'm not ready.

05:53.000 --> 05:54.000
Said Brian.

05:54.000 --> 05:56.000
I'm not either.

05:56.000 --> 05:58.000
I didn't look at my notes.

05:58.000 --> 05:59.000
Said Jim.

05:59.000 --> 06:02.000
The bus came and they got on.

06:02.000 --> 06:05.000
They saw their school friends and started talking.

06:05.000 --> 06:10.000
The bus was always crowded, but the bus ride was fun.

06:10.000 --> 06:16.000
When they got near Galileo High School, they could smell the chocolate from the chocolate factory nearby.

06:16.000 --> 06:19.000
They loved the smell of the chocolate.

06:19.000 --> 06:21.000
It made them hungry.

06:21.000 --> 06:24.000
The math test was difficult.

06:24.000 --> 06:28.000
The students were happy when it was finally lunchtime.

06:28.000 --> 06:31.000
They all went to the big school cafeteria.

06:31.000 --> 06:33.000
Why is math so difficult?

06:33.000 --> 06:34.000
Said Jim.

06:34.000 --> 06:37.000
I think Mrs. Miller makes the test difficult.

06:37.000 --> 06:40.000
Don't worry about the test and eat your lunch.

06:40.000 --> 06:41.000
Said Brian.

06:41.000 --> 06:45.000
In the afternoon, they had a long science lesson.

06:45.000 --> 06:47.000
It was very interesting.

06:47.000 --> 06:50.000
They studied chemistry in the school laboratory.

06:50.000 --> 06:55.000
They often did experiments with their chemistry teacher, Mr. Woods.

06:55.000 --> 06:57.000
They liked Mr. Woods.

06:57.000 --> 07:01.000
At a quarter past three, the school bell rang.

07:01.000 --> 07:04.000
It was time to go home and it was Friday.

07:04.000 --> 07:05.000
What are you doing this weekend?

07:05.000 --> 07:06.000
Ask Brian.

07:06.000 --> 07:08.000
I'm working at the supermarket tomorrow.

07:08.000 --> 07:09.000
Said Jim.

07:09.000 --> 07:12.000
But on Sunday, I'm coming to see your basketball game.

07:12.000 --> 07:14.000
I hope we win.

07:14.000 --> 07:15.000
Said Brian.

07:15.000 --> 07:18.000
I'm working tomorrow as well at my parents' grocery store.

07:18.000 --> 07:21.000
It's always a busy day, but I'm free tomorrow night.

07:21.000 --> 07:25.000
Well, I'm babysitting for the Moreno children all weekend.

07:25.000 --> 07:26.000
Said Susan.

07:26.000 --> 07:29.000
Do you want to go to the movies tomorrow night, Jim?

07:29.000 --> 07:30.000
Ask Brian.

07:30.000 --> 07:32.000
Yes, that's a great idea.

07:32.000 --> 07:33.000
Said Jim.

07:33.000 --> 07:34.000
I'll phone you.

07:36.000 --> 07:44.000
So that's it.

07:44.000 --> 07:56.000
Chapter 2, The Face at the Window

07:56.000 --> 07:59.000
Jim walked slowly up Telegraph Hill.

07:59.000 --> 08:01.000
It was a foggy afternoon in February.

08:01.000 --> 08:10.000
Every day, Jim walked in front of an old mansion. It was a mysterious wooden building with a big garden and a fence around it.

08:10.000 --> 08:17.000
Jim often looked at it and thought, what's inside? Why doesn't anyone live here?

08:17.000 --> 08:28.000
That afternoon, he stopped in front of the gate. He looked at the garden and the trees. What a strange place. No one took care of it.

08:28.000 --> 08:42.000
Then he looked up at the old mansion. He looked at the window on the second floor. There was a face behind it. He felt cold. It was the face of a little girl with long dark hair.

08:42.000 --> 08:56.000
But no one lived in that mansion. Who was it? A ghost? Jim didn't believe in ghosts. But who was the girl at the window? She looked down at him.

08:56.000 --> 09:09.000
He continued looking at the window. Suddenly the face of the girl disappeared. Jim could not see well because it was very foggy. He decided to go home quickly.

09:09.000 --> 09:15.000
He walked in the door and into the living room. He saw his grandfather in the corner of the room.

09:16.000 --> 09:23.000
Grandpa, he cried, I saw a ghost. What did you say? Asked his grandfather with a smile.

09:23.000 --> 09:31.000
I saw the face of a little girl at the window of the old mansion. No one lives there but I saw a girl. She looked at me.

09:31.000 --> 09:43.000
Are you sure Jim? It's a very foggy afternoon. Did you see her clearly? No one lives in the old steward mansion.

09:43.000 --> 09:52.000
It's about 100 years old. There's a strange story about it. But I don't think there are any ghosts.

09:52.000 --> 10:07.000
What story? Please tell me. Said Jim. Well, Mr. Stewart was a very rich but very strange man. He was very interested in science and experiments.

10:08.000 --> 10:21.000
He had a lot of enemies. People thought his experiments were mysterious and sinister. His wife and daughter died in a mysterious accident. It was terrible.

10:21.000 --> 10:29.000
He left San Francisco and returned to New York. I saw a face, Grandpa. I did. Said Jim.

10:30.000 --> 10:39.000
But Jim, you don't believe in ghosts? Said his grandfather. You're right. But I saw that girl's face. Said Jim.

10:39.000 --> 10:52.000
Maybe it was your imagination. Said his grandfather kindly. Jim went to his room and turned on the radio. He listened to some songs and then started doing his homework.

10:53.000 --> 11:06.000
The next day, Jim went to work at the supermarket. It was a busy day. A strange man with long hair and a silver earring came in. His clothes were old.

11:06.000 --> 11:18.000
Customers were usually friendly, but this man was not. He had an angry expression, paid quickly and left. It was something strange about him.

11:19.000 --> 11:37.000
When Jim went home that evening, he phoned Brian. Hi. How was your day? Very busy. Said Brian. Yes. Mine too. Do you want to see that new science fiction movie on at the Big Screen Movie Theater? We can meet at 7 p.m. in front of the park. Said Jim.

11:37.000 --> 11:43.000
Okay. I'll see you then. Said Brian. At Washington Square. Don't be late.

11:43.000 --> 11:53.000
Jim left the house and started walking to the park. He stopped in front of the gate of the old Stuart Mansion again. There was no one at the window.

11:53.000 --> 12:10.000
He stayed there a few minutes. It was windy and the big trees in the garden made strange noises. He looked at his watch. It was nearly 7 o'clock. He was late to meet Brian.

12:11.000 --> 12:25.000
Excuse me. What time does the next cable car leave? Well, they go every 20 minutes. So the next one will leave at 10 to 11. That's in 10 minutes.

12:25.000 --> 12:37.000
Two. Tickets on sale here for a guided tour of Alcatraz. Next tour starts in half an hour at a quarter past three.

12:38.000 --> 12:51.000
Three. What time shall we meet? Well, I finish work at 7 o'clock and Washington Square is very near. Let's meet at five past seven. Is that okay?

12:51.000 --> 13:02.000
Four. Jim, why are you late for school? I'm sorry, sir, but there was a problem with the bus and it didn't leave until 9 30.

13:03.000 --> 13:08.000
Five. Hi, Susan. What time are you finishing work today?

13:08.000 --> 13:20.000
Well, Mrs. Moreno first asked me to work only in the morning and finish at around half past 12 or 20 to 1. But then she asked me to also look after the children during the afternoon as well.

13:20.000 --> 13:25.000
So I'll finish between half past five and quarter to six.

13:33.000 --> 13:38.000
Chapter three. The Stewart Mansion.

13:42.000 --> 13:49.000
After the movies, the two boys went to eat an ice cream at Pier 39. It was a beautiful night.

13:49.000 --> 13:55.000
They stopped and looked at Alcatraz Island in the middle of San Francisco Bay.

13:55.000 --> 13:59.000
Jim told Brian about the face at the window.

13:59.000 --> 14:06.000
What? Said Brian. I don't believe it. I want to come with you next week. I want to see her too.

14:06.000 --> 14:16.000
Really? That's great. Said Jim. It's a strange place. I'm always a little frayed when I go alone. Let's go together soon.

14:16.000 --> 14:22.000
On Monday after school, the two friends met Susan at the bus stop. They got on the bus.

14:22.000 --> 14:27.000
Where are you going? Susan asked. Can you keep a secret?

14:27.000 --> 14:34.000
Ask Jim. Why do you have a secret? Ask Susan. Yes, I do. Said Jim.

14:34.000 --> 14:41.000
Is it about Jenny Lee's new boyfriend? Ask Susan. Jenny was a very popular girl in their class.

14:41.000 --> 14:46.000
Susan hoped Jenny Lee's new boyfriend wasn't Jim.

14:46.000 --> 14:50.000
He told her about the Stewart Mansion and about the face at the window.

14:50.000 --> 14:58.000
Then he told his friends his grandfather's story about the mansion, the scientist and the mysterious accident.

14:58.000 --> 15:06.000
Scary. Said Susan. Old mansions always have ghosts. Can I come with you?

15:06.000 --> 15:12.000
Jim smiled at her and said, of course, but promise not to tell anyone.

15:12.000 --> 15:17.000
Jim was happy that Susan wanted to come. Susan was pretty.

15:17.000 --> 15:22.000
Hey, come on. It's our stop. Said Brian. Let's get off.

15:22.000 --> 15:30.000
It was 4.30 p.m. and it was a cold, sunny afternoon. The three friends walked up Telegraph Hill.

15:30.000 --> 15:35.000
When they arrived at the Stewart Mansion, they stopped in front of the old gate.

15:35.000 --> 15:42.000
What a strange place. Said Susan. It's cool, said Brian.

15:42.000 --> 15:47.000
They looked at the window on the second floor, but they saw nothing.

15:47.000 --> 15:50.000
They started talking and looking around.

15:50.000 --> 15:57.000
Hey, do you smell anything strange? Said Susan. They stopped and smelled the air.

15:57.000 --> 16:00.000
There was a very bad smell in the air.

16:00.000 --> 16:07.000
What is that smell? asked Brian. I don't know. It smells like rotten eggs.

16:07.000 --> 16:11.000
Said Jim. Yes, that's true. But where is it coming from?

16:11.000 --> 16:19.000
asked Brian. Susan and Brian looked at Jim. Then they looked at the window on the second floor again.

16:19.000 --> 16:26.000
Are you sure you saw a face, Jim? asked Susan. Jim didn't know what to say.

16:26.000 --> 16:33.000
There was no one at the window now. This is a scary place, but I don't see any ghosts.

16:33.000 --> 16:38.000
Said Brian. This smell is terrible. Said Susan.

16:38.000 --> 16:43.000
Let's go home and forget about the ghost. It was probably your imagination, Jim.

16:43.000 --> 16:47.000
Look, cry Jim. There's yellow smoke over there.

16:47.000 --> 16:53.000
Near the bottom window of the mansion, they saw strange yellow smoke in the air.

16:53.000 --> 16:58.000
Wow, you're right. Said Susan. What's happening here? Said Brian.

16:58.000 --> 17:03.000
It smells like a dead body. Maybe there's a dead body in the mansion.

17:03.000 --> 17:10.000
Maybe this is a secret cemetery. Said Jim. Brian's face became white.

17:10.000 --> 17:17.000
The three friends looked at each other. A secret cemetery? They said softly.

17:17.000 --> 17:24.000
They were curious, but terrified at the same time. No one knew what to say.

17:24.000 --> 17:29.000
Oh please, let's go home. This place frightens me. Said Susan.

17:29.000 --> 17:33.000
There's something strange happening here. Said Brian.

17:33.000 --> 17:38.000
They agreed to leave and went to Jim's house to listen to his new CDs.

17:38.000 --> 17:42.000
They sat in Jim's room and talked about the mansion.

17:42.000 --> 17:49.000
Then Susan suddenly said, Hey, there's the big Chinese New Year parade this Saturday night.

17:49.000 --> 17:54.000
I'm taking the Moreno children. It's always lots of fun. Said Jim.

17:54.000 --> 17:58.000
I'm going to go. Me too. Said Brian.

18:00.000 --> 18:04.000
A guide to San Francisco.

18:04.000 --> 18:12.000
San Francisco is an international center for business, education, science, and the arts.

18:12.000 --> 18:19.000
Thousands of tourists visit the city every year because there are many interesting places to see.

18:19.000 --> 18:26.000
San Francisco is a very cosmopolitan city. People from all over the world live there.

18:26.000 --> 18:31.000
There are a lot of multicultural neighborhoods.

18:31.000 --> 18:38.000
Chinatown is a very big, colorful Chinese neighborhood on Grant Avenue.

18:38.000 --> 18:45.000
The streets here are narrow. There are Chinese food shops, souvenir shops and restaurants.

18:45.000 --> 18:50.000
There are also Chinese libraries and Chinese schools.

18:50.000 --> 18:56.000
Many children from Chinese families go to Chinese school after regular school.

18:56.000 --> 19:01.000
They want to learn to speak, read, and write their parents' language.

19:01.000 --> 19:07.000
The street signs and shop signs in Chinatown are in Chinese too.

19:07.000 --> 19:12.000
Alcatraz Island is a small island in San Francisco Bay.

19:12.000 --> 19:18.000
It is a big tourist attraction because it was a famous prison for many years.

19:18.000 --> 19:22.000
There was one guard or every three to five prisoners.

19:22.000 --> 19:27.000
Some prisoners tried to escape, but they failed.

19:27.000 --> 19:35.000
It was impossible to escape from Alcatraz by swimming across to San Francisco because of the cold water.

19:35.000 --> 19:42.000
Alcatraz was home to many dangerous criminals, like the gangster, Al Capone.

19:43.000 --> 19:49.000
The prison was closed in 1963 because the conditions were very bad.

19:49.000 --> 19:52.000
Now, it is a museum.

19:52.000 --> 19:57.000
You can see photographs of some of the prisoners there and read about them.

19:57.000 --> 20:03.000
There are many exciting movies about Alcatraz Island and its prisoners.

20:03.000 --> 20:07.000
Pier 39 is another famous attraction on the bay.

20:07.000 --> 20:15.000
There are many different shops, games galleries, ice cream stands, and entertainments on the pier.

20:15.000 --> 20:19.000
Many of the shops sell funny t-shirts.

20:19.000 --> 20:22.000
Fisherman's Wharf is on the bay too.

20:22.000 --> 20:28.000
There are hundreds of fishing boats and outdoor food stands with good seafood.

20:28.000 --> 20:32.000
There are also many street artists and souvenir shops.

20:33.000 --> 20:38.000
At Fisherman's Wharf, you can take an exciting boat ride on the bay.

20:38.000 --> 20:44.000
Remember to wear warm clothes because it's sometimes very windy on the bay.

20:44.000 --> 20:49.000
The cable car is a common form of transportation in San Francisco.

20:49.000 --> 20:53.000
It climbs up and down the city's hills.

20:53.000 --> 20:57.000
It is great fun to ride the cable car.

20:57.000 --> 21:02.000
Golden Gate Park is a big park in the middle of the city.

21:02.000 --> 21:09.000
There are many excellent museums, a famous aquarium, and a flower conservatory.

21:09.000 --> 21:15.000
You can also ride your bike or go jogging in this beautiful park.

21:15.000 --> 21:20.000
A great symbol of San Francisco is the Golden Gate Bridge.

21:20.000 --> 21:25.000
It is a spectacular bridge with its red orange color.

21:25.000 --> 21:33.000
It was very difficult to build it in 1937 because of the strong winds and rough sea.

21:33.000 --> 21:37.000
It connects San Francisco to Northern California.

21:37.000 --> 21:41.000
Another bridge connects the city to Eastern California.

21:41.000 --> 21:46.000
This is called the Bay Bridge.

21:46.000 --> 21:49.000
Union Square is in the city center.

21:50.000 --> 21:58.000
It is an international shopping area with many famous designer shops and big department stores.

21:58.000 --> 22:02.000
There are many tall buildings in the center of San Francisco.

22:02.000 --> 22:05.000
They are called skyscrapers.

22:05.000 --> 22:11.000
One skyscraper looks like a giant triangle.

22:11.000 --> 22:16.000
The weather in San Francisco is often foggy and windy.

22:16.000 --> 22:19.000
It doesn't rain a lot.

22:19.000 --> 22:25.000
A lot of people go to live in San Francisco because it has so many attractions.

22:25.000 --> 22:37.000
The people of San Francisco are very popular in America because they are usually very friendly and outgoing.

22:38.000 --> 22:47.000
Chapter 4. Chinese New Year

22:51.000 --> 22:54.000
This was the year of the dragon.

22:54.000 --> 22:57.000
The Chinese believe that the dragon brings good luck.

22:57.000 --> 23:02.000
The Chinese New Year parade is a very big event in San Francisco.

23:02.000 --> 23:09.000
It always takes place on a Saturday night between January 21st and February 19th.

23:09.000 --> 23:12.000
The date depends on the position of the moon.

23:12.000 --> 23:15.000
Thousands of people go to see the parade every year.

23:15.000 --> 23:23.000
There are many beautiful costumes, Chinese music, and Grand Avenue is decorated with colorful lanterns.

23:23.000 --> 23:27.000
A long paper dragon moves along Grand Avenue.

23:27.000 --> 23:31.000
There are firecrackers and lots of noise.

23:31.000 --> 23:34.000
Jim and Brian took the cable car to Grand Avenue.

23:34.000 --> 23:38.000
It was always fun to ride the cable car.

23:38.000 --> 23:41.000
Susan and their high school friends were at the parade.

23:41.000 --> 23:44.000
Jenny Lee was there with her new boyfriend.

23:44.000 --> 23:48.000
He was the captain of the football team and he was handsome.

23:48.000 --> 23:51.000
There was a big crowd everywhere.

23:51.000 --> 23:58.000
Suddenly, on the other side of the street, Jim saw the face of the little girl at the window in the crowd.

23:58.000 --> 24:00.000
Jim told Brian,

24:00.000 --> 24:02.000
Let's follow her.

24:02.000 --> 24:03.000
Said Brian.

24:03.000 --> 24:08.000
It was difficult to move because there were lots of people everywhere.

24:08.000 --> 24:11.000
Then the big paper dragon appeared in the parade.

24:11.000 --> 24:15.000
The little girl suddenly disappeared behind the long dragon.

24:15.000 --> 24:18.000
How can anyone disappear so quickly?

24:18.000 --> 24:19.000
Said Jim.

24:19.000 --> 24:22.000
They went back to watch the parade.

24:22.000 --> 24:25.000
Maybe she is a ghost, he thought.

24:25.000 --> 24:27.000
The weekend passed quickly.

24:27.000 --> 24:30.000
It was Monday morning and they were at school.

24:30.000 --> 24:34.000
Brian and Jim told Susan about the girl.

24:34.000 --> 24:37.000
Now she wanted to explore the Stuart Mansion too.

24:37.000 --> 24:40.000
They made plans during lunch.

24:40.000 --> 24:43.000
Let's go this evening after dinner.

24:43.000 --> 24:46.000
Remember to bring a flashlight and wear dark clothes.

24:46.000 --> 24:48.000
Said Jim.

24:48.000 --> 24:50.000
They were very excited.

24:50.000 --> 24:54.000
When school finished at 3.15 p.m. they ran out.

24:54.000 --> 24:57.000
They wanted to go home quickly.

24:57.000 --> 25:03.000
At about 7 p.m., they met in front of Jim's house on Telegraph Hill.

25:03.000 --> 25:07.000
When they arrived at the Stuart Mansion, everything was dark.

25:07.000 --> 25:10.000
It was a foggy, windy night.

25:10.000 --> 25:14.000
They looked at the window on the second floor, but there was no one there.

25:14.000 --> 25:18.000
They climbed over the fence and went into the garden.

25:18.000 --> 25:21.000
The tall trees moved in the wind.

25:22.000 --> 25:24.000
I don't smell anything this time.

25:24.000 --> 25:25.000
Said Susan.

25:25.000 --> 25:26.000
Me neither.

25:26.000 --> 25:27.000
Agree Jim.

25:27.000 --> 25:29.000
And now what do we do?

25:29.000 --> 25:30.000
Ask Brian.

25:30.000 --> 25:31.000
I don't know.

25:31.000 --> 25:32.000
Said Jim.

25:32.000 --> 25:34.000
Let's look inside.

25:34.000 --> 25:37.000
There are windows near the ground.

25:37.000 --> 25:38.000
Said Susan.

25:38.000 --> 25:41.000
And let's remember to be very quiet.

25:41.000 --> 25:42.000
She whispered.

25:42.000 --> 25:43.000
Okay.

25:43.000 --> 25:44.000
Said Jim.

25:44.000 --> 25:49.000
The three friends went to a window and looked inside.

25:49.000 --> 25:52.000
The glass was old and dirty.

25:52.000 --> 25:55.000
Brian turned on his flashlight and looked.

25:55.000 --> 25:59.000
It was a small room with an old desk and some chairs.

25:59.000 --> 26:01.000
This was probably the study.

26:01.000 --> 26:02.000
Said Brian.

26:02.000 --> 26:04.000
Susan turned on her flashlight.

26:04.000 --> 26:07.000
Look at the newspaper on the desk.

26:07.000 --> 26:08.000
Said Susan.

26:08.000 --> 26:12.000
I can't see well, but I think it's yesterday's newspaper.

26:12.000 --> 26:14.000
Look at the headline.

26:14.000 --> 26:16.000
Water's scarce in San Francisco.

26:16.000 --> 26:18.000
But no one lives here.

26:18.000 --> 26:19.000
Said Jim.

26:19.000 --> 26:25.000
They looked inside another window and saw a big room with old furniture.

26:25.000 --> 26:27.000
It looked like the living room.

26:27.000 --> 26:33.000
On the wall there was a big painting of a man, a woman, and a little girl.

26:33.000 --> 26:34.000
Look.

26:34.000 --> 26:36.000
That's probably a painting of the Stuart family.

26:36.000 --> 26:37.000
Said Susan.

26:37.000 --> 26:38.000
Yes.

26:38.000 --> 26:40.000
Before the mysterious accident.

26:40.000 --> 26:41.000
Said Jim.

26:41.000 --> 26:44.000
And the little girl has long dark hair.

26:44.000 --> 26:47.000
She looks like the girl at the window.

26:47.000 --> 26:48.000
Said Susan.

26:48.000 --> 26:50.000
But we saw the little girl at the parade.

26:50.000 --> 26:51.000
Said Brian.

26:51.000 --> 26:53.000
How can she be a ghost?

26:53.000 --> 26:57.000
Remember, she disappeared behind the dragon very quickly.

26:57.000 --> 26:59.000
Said Jim.

26:59.000 --> 27:02.000
They went to the other side of the mansion.

27:02.000 --> 27:05.000
It was a broken window near the bottom of the house.

27:05.000 --> 27:07.000
They looked inside.

27:07.000 --> 27:09.000
They saw a big dark basement.

27:09.000 --> 27:11.000
No one was there.

27:11.000 --> 27:14.000
Then Jim turned on his flashlight, too.

27:14.000 --> 27:17.000
In the basement, they saw some long tables.

27:17.000 --> 27:22.000
There were test tubes, glass bottles, and other laboratory equipment.

27:22.000 --> 27:26.000
This looks like our chemistry lab, said Jim.

27:26.000 --> 27:28.000
Maybe someone is using it.

27:28.000 --> 27:29.000
Said Susan.

27:29.000 --> 27:30.000
But why?

27:30.000 --> 27:32.000
Maybe someone is experimenting.

27:32.000 --> 27:34.000
With something secret.

27:34.000 --> 27:35.000
Said Brian.

27:35.000 --> 27:37.000
I don't like this place.

27:37.000 --> 27:38.000
Said Susan.

27:39.000 --> 27:41.000
It gives me a bad feeling.

27:41.000 --> 27:42.000
Are you scared?

27:42.000 --> 27:43.000
Ask Brian.

27:43.000 --> 27:44.000
No.

27:44.000 --> 27:46.000
I want to come back again, but in the daytime.

27:46.000 --> 27:47.000
Said Susan.

27:47.000 --> 27:48.000
Okay.

27:48.000 --> 27:49.000
Said Jim.

27:49.000 --> 27:51.000
Let's go then.

27:51.000 --> 27:52.000
Crash.

27:52.000 --> 27:54.000
There was a loud noise.

27:54.000 --> 27:56.000
It came from one of the rooms upstairs.

27:56.000 --> 27:57.000
What was that?

27:57.000 --> 27:58.000
Cried Susan.

27:58.000 --> 28:00.000
We're not alone here.

28:00.000 --> 28:03.000
Someone or something is here.

28:03.000 --> 28:04.000
Said Jim.

28:04.000 --> 28:05.000
Let's get out of here.

28:05.000 --> 28:06.000
Said Brian.

28:06.000 --> 28:08.000
They started running to the fence.

28:08.000 --> 28:14.000
They ran under the trees and suddenly heard a strange sound from the branches above their heads.

28:14.000 --> 28:15.000
They looked up.

28:15.000 --> 28:16.000
Eek.

28:16.000 --> 28:17.000
Cried Susan.

28:17.000 --> 28:18.000
That's.

28:18.000 --> 28:22.000
They climbed over the fence quickly and ran away.

28:22.000 --> 28:32.000
Chapter five.

28:32.000 --> 28:40.000
A mysterious magician.

28:40.000 --> 28:44.000
Jim heard the voice of a child in the fog.

28:44.000 --> 28:45.000
Help.

28:45.000 --> 28:46.000
Help.

28:46.000 --> 28:48.000
It was a cold night.

28:48.000 --> 28:51.000
Jim stood in front of the Stuart mansion.

28:51.000 --> 28:53.000
There was fog everywhere.

28:53.000 --> 28:56.000
The voice came from inside the mansion.

28:56.000 --> 28:58.000
He didn't know what to do.

28:58.000 --> 29:02.000
He wanted to help the child, but he also wanted to run away.

29:02.000 --> 29:05.000
Suddenly he felt a hand on his arm.

29:05.000 --> 29:07.000
For a moment his heart stopped.

29:07.000 --> 29:08.000
He could not turn around.

29:08.000 --> 29:10.000
He was too scared.

29:10.000 --> 29:13.000
An angry voice behind him said.

29:13.000 --> 29:15.000
What do you want?

29:15.000 --> 29:17.000
Jim turned around slowly.

29:17.000 --> 29:22.000
He saw a big man with long dark hair and angry eyes.

29:22.000 --> 29:26.000
It's the same man I saw at the supermarket two weeks ago.

29:26.000 --> 29:27.000
He thought.

29:27.000 --> 29:31.000
He was about fifty years old.

29:31.000 --> 29:34.000
He had a silver tooth and it shone in the dark.

29:34.000 --> 29:36.000
He also had a silver earring.

29:36.000 --> 29:38.000
He was awful.

29:38.000 --> 29:39.000
Well?

29:39.000 --> 29:41.000
What do you want here?

29:41.000 --> 29:43.000
Jim looked at him and said.

29:43.000 --> 29:44.000
Nothing.

29:44.000 --> 29:45.000
Nothing.

29:45.000 --> 29:46.000
Who are you?

29:46.000 --> 29:48.000
Don't ask questions.

29:48.000 --> 29:49.000
Stay away from here.

29:49.000 --> 29:51.000
I'm a dangerous man.

29:51.000 --> 29:54.000
I eliminate problems and you're a problem.

29:54.000 --> 29:55.000
Go away.

29:55.000 --> 29:56.000
Now.

29:56.000 --> 30:00.000
He pushed Jim to the ground and disappeared in the fog.

30:00.000 --> 30:01.000
Jim woke up.

30:01.000 --> 30:03.000
He was scared.

30:03.000 --> 30:04.000
Phew.

30:04.000 --> 30:06.000
It was only a dream.

30:06.000 --> 30:07.000
He thought.

30:07.000 --> 30:09.000
He looked at his alarm clock.

30:09.000 --> 30:13.000
It was three a.m.

30:13.000 --> 30:19.000
The next day Jim, Brian and Susan went back to the mansion in the afternoon.

30:19.000 --> 30:21.000
They went to the basement window.

30:21.000 --> 30:23.000
No one was there.

30:23.000 --> 30:27.000
But there was a big black book on one of the tables.

30:27.000 --> 30:30.000
Someone was here last night or this morning.

30:30.000 --> 30:32.000
There's a book on the table.

30:32.000 --> 30:34.000
It wasn't here last night.

30:34.000 --> 30:35.000
Said Jim.

30:35.000 --> 30:36.000
You're right.

30:36.000 --> 30:37.000
Said Brian.

30:37.000 --> 30:39.000
And who has the keys to the mansion?

30:39.000 --> 30:41.000
Ask Susan.

30:41.000 --> 30:43.000
That's a good question.

30:43.000 --> 30:45.000
Said Brian.

30:45.000 --> 30:49.000
The days passed and something else happened.

30:49.000 --> 30:52.000
The grass in Washington Square was green again.

30:52.000 --> 30:54.000
And there were flowers.

30:54.000 --> 30:57.000
Everyone in the neighborhood was surprised and happy.

30:57.000 --> 31:00.000
Jim talked with his grandfather about this.

31:00.000 --> 31:03.000
Grandpa, it's amazing.

31:03.000 --> 31:05.000
Washington Square is beautiful again.

31:05.000 --> 31:08.000
The grass and the flowers are growing.

31:08.000 --> 31:09.000
But how?

31:09.000 --> 31:11.000
There's no rain.

31:11.000 --> 31:14.000
How can grass and flowers grow without water?

31:14.000 --> 31:15.000
Said Jim.

31:15.000 --> 31:16.000
You're right.

31:16.000 --> 31:18.000
It's strange.

31:18.000 --> 31:21.000
There's no rain, but the grass is growing.

31:21.000 --> 31:22.000
Said Grandpa.

31:22.000 --> 31:25.000
There's an article in today's newspaper about it.

31:25.000 --> 31:27.000
Jim started reading.

31:27.000 --> 31:31.000
The grass and flowers are growing again in Washington Square.

31:31.000 --> 31:36.000
The square was dry for months, but now it is beautiful and green.

31:36.000 --> 31:40.000
The organizer of the Jazz Festival, Mike Murphy, says,

31:40.000 --> 31:43.000
I thought it wasn't possible to have the Jazz Festival this year.

31:43.000 --> 31:46.000
But now it's beautiful and we can have the festival as we always do.

31:46.000 --> 31:50.000
Artists from all over California are coming this year.

31:50.000 --> 31:55.000
Some people believe something mysterious is happening in Washington Square.

31:55.000 --> 32:00.000
One person said, there's no rain, but the grass and the flowers are growing.

32:00.000 --> 32:05.000
I don't believe in magic, but it's very strange.

32:05.000 --> 32:07.000
Who is the magician?

32:07.000 --> 32:11.000
Mr. Magician, can you bring San Francisco some rain too?

32:23.000 --> 32:32.000
Chapter 6, The Game

32:32.000 --> 32:36.000
One afternoon, Susan took the Moreno children to Washington Square.

32:36.000 --> 32:39.000
They played in the small playground.

32:39.000 --> 32:41.000
Then they went to the duck pond.

32:41.000 --> 32:46.000
The children liked feeding the ducks in the pond, but the ducks were not hungry.

32:46.000 --> 32:50.000
Susie, why aren't the ducks eating the bread?

32:50.000 --> 32:52.000
Asked little Sally Moreno.

32:52.000 --> 32:53.000
I don't know.

32:53.000 --> 32:54.000
It's strange.

32:54.000 --> 32:56.000
They're usually hungry.

32:56.000 --> 32:58.000
The fish aren't hungry either.

32:58.000 --> 32:59.000
Said Susan.

32:59.000 --> 33:02.000
Well, it's half past five and it's time to go home.

33:02.000 --> 33:06.000
The next morning there was a big crowd at Washington Square.

33:06.000 --> 33:10.000
Jim, Brian, and Susan were there with many other people.

33:10.000 --> 33:13.000
Everyone was at the duck pond.

33:13.000 --> 33:17.000
Some of the ducks were dead and others were sick.

33:17.000 --> 33:19.000
Lots of fish were dead too.

33:19.000 --> 33:21.000
This is terrible.

33:21.000 --> 33:22.000
Said Susan.

33:22.000 --> 33:24.000
Someone poisoned those poor ducks.

33:24.000 --> 33:26.000
Said Jim.

33:26.000 --> 33:30.000
At that moment, the bus came and the students got on.

33:30.000 --> 33:34.000
On the bus, everyone continued talking about the ducks.

33:34.000 --> 33:39.000
Early the next morning, Jim's grandfather bought the newspaper.

33:39.000 --> 33:43.000
During breakfast, this is what they read.

33:43.000 --> 33:50.000
Eight ducks and many fish were found dead in the pond in Washington Square yesterday morning.

33:50.000 --> 33:54.000
Only last week, people came to see the jazz festival.

33:54.000 --> 33:56.000
It was a great success.

33:56.000 --> 34:04.000
A scientist analyzed the grass and the water in the pond and found a high quantity of a new chemical.

34:04.000 --> 34:09.000
The new chemical is similar to greenex, but it is more toxic.

34:09.000 --> 34:13.000
Greenex was a popular fertilizer 20 years ago.

34:13.000 --> 34:17.000
It is illegal to use it today, the scientist said.

34:17.000 --> 34:23.000
The volunteer organization Helping Hands is now looking after the sick ducks.

34:23.000 --> 34:29.000
Volunteers can call this number 3920369.

34:29.000 --> 34:34.000
The San Francisco Police Department are investigating the case.

34:34.000 --> 34:35.000
Wow!

34:35.000 --> 34:36.000
Exclaimed Jim.

34:36.000 --> 34:40.000
This mysterious new chemical is responsible for the green grass.

34:40.000 --> 34:44.000
So someone created a new fertilizer and it's toxic.

34:44.000 --> 34:47.000
What irresponsible people?

34:47.000 --> 34:49.000
Said Jim's grandfather.

34:49.000 --> 34:51.000
Think of the children.

34:51.000 --> 34:54.000
They play in Washington Square.

34:54.000 --> 34:58.000
On Thursday evening, Jim and Brian were at Susan's house.

34:58.000 --> 35:01.000
This fertilizer thing is so strange.

35:01.000 --> 35:03.000
Maybe it's a mad scientist.

35:03.000 --> 35:05.000
Said Brian.

35:05.000 --> 35:08.000
Maybe they can make a lot of money with this new fertilizer.

35:08.000 --> 35:09.000
Said Jim.

35:09.000 --> 35:10.000
Yes, a lot of money.

35:10.000 --> 35:12.000
And they'll poison all the animals.

35:12.000 --> 35:14.000
Said Brian.

35:14.000 --> 35:16.000
Susan was quiet for a few minutes.

35:16.000 --> 35:17.000
Then she said.

35:17.000 --> 35:20.000
I want to solve this mystery.

35:20.000 --> 35:27.000
I think there's a connection between the Stuart Mansion and this fertilizer, but I don't know.

35:27.000 --> 35:32.000
On Friday evening, Susan went to see her brother's football game.

35:32.000 --> 35:37.000
It was San Francisco University versus Monterey University.

35:37.000 --> 35:39.000
Tom was a good player.

35:39.000 --> 35:41.000
The stadium was almost full.

35:41.000 --> 35:45.000
Susan found a good seat to watch the game.

35:45.000 --> 35:47.000
Susan liked football games.

35:47.000 --> 35:50.000
She always went to watch her brother play.

35:50.000 --> 35:54.000
It was a cold night and she put her hands in her pockets.

35:54.000 --> 35:56.000
I'm glad I have a warm jacket.

35:56.000 --> 35:57.000
She thought.

35:57.000 --> 35:59.000
Then she looked at her watch.

35:59.000 --> 36:01.000
It was almost half past eight.

36:01.000 --> 36:04.000
It was time for the big game to start.

36:04.000 --> 36:06.000
She was excited.

36:06.000 --> 36:11.000
Suddenly, two people behind her started talking about Washington Square.

36:11.000 --> 36:14.000
But she could not hear all of their conversation

36:14.000 --> 36:16.000
because there was lots of noise.

36:16.000 --> 36:18.000
She listened carefully.

36:18.000 --> 36:20.000
Can't test anymore.

36:20.000 --> 36:21.000
Not now.

36:21.000 --> 36:23.000
Said one young woman.

36:23.000 --> 36:24.000
Too dangerous.

36:24.000 --> 36:26.000
Said the other.

36:26.000 --> 36:28.000
These people know something.

36:28.000 --> 36:29.000
Thought Susan.

36:29.000 --> 36:33.000
She continued listening, but she did not look at them.

36:33.000 --> 36:37.000
It's illegal, but the experiment almost finished.

36:37.000 --> 36:39.000
Said one voice.

36:39.000 --> 36:40.000
All right.

36:40.000 --> 36:41.000
On Lombard Street.

36:41.000 --> 36:43.000
Said the other voice.

36:43.000 --> 36:44.000
On Lombard Street.

36:44.000 --> 36:47.000
The Stuart Mansion is on Lombard Street.

36:47.000 --> 36:52.000
So there is a connection between the mansion and Washington Square.

36:52.000 --> 36:54.000
Susan thought.

36:54.000 --> 36:56.000
Suddenly, she understood.

36:56.000 --> 36:58.000
I must tell Jim and Brian.

36:58.000 --> 36:59.000
She thought.

36:59.000 --> 37:03.000
She was very excited and looked at her watch.

37:03.000 --> 37:08.000
The game finished on time and San Francisco University won.

37:08.000 --> 37:11.000
After the game, she phoned Jim.

37:11.000 --> 37:15.000
She told him about the conversation between the two young women.

37:15.000 --> 37:17.000
You're a great detective, Susan.

37:17.000 --> 37:18.000
You're right.

37:18.000 --> 37:20.000
It's that secret laboratory.

37:20.000 --> 37:21.000
Said Jim.

37:21.000 --> 37:23.000
Let's tell the police immediately.

37:23.000 --> 37:24.000
Said Susan.

37:24.000 --> 37:25.000
Yes.

37:25.000 --> 37:27.000
That's the right thing to do.

37:27.000 --> 37:28.000
Tomorrow's Saturday.

37:28.000 --> 37:30.000
Let's meet early in the morning.

37:30.000 --> 37:31.000
Said Jim.

37:31.000 --> 37:34.000
I'll call the supermarket and tell them I can't work.

37:34.000 --> 37:35.000
Okay.

37:35.000 --> 37:36.000
Said Susan.

37:36.000 --> 37:38.000
I'll call Brian now.

37:38.000 --> 37:41.000
It was lucky I went to Tom's football game.

37:41.000 --> 37:42.000
She thought.

37:46.000 --> 37:50.000
Natural resources and pollution.

37:50.000 --> 37:54.000
Natural resources are the most important things on our planet.

37:54.000 --> 37:57.000
We cannot live without them.

37:57.000 --> 38:00.000
There are many kinds of natural resources.

38:00.000 --> 38:07.000
Light, air, water, soil, plants and wildlife are all natural resources.

38:07.000 --> 38:11.000
Water is an essential natural resource.

38:11.000 --> 38:16.000
Water is becoming scarce and many people continue to waste it,

38:16.000 --> 38:19.000
especially in western countries.

38:19.000 --> 38:23.000
In many countries, people do not have enough.

38:23.000 --> 38:29.000
Sometimes people die in these countries because they cannot find clean water to drink.

38:29.000 --> 38:33.000
Air is another essential natural resource.

38:33.000 --> 38:39.000
Cars, factories and toxic chemicals all create air pollution.

38:39.000 --> 38:45.000
Pollution damages the quality of our air, especially in big cities.

38:45.000 --> 38:51.000
This means that some children and adults have problems when they breathe.

38:51.000 --> 38:57.000
Air pollution also contaminates the rain because of the large quantity of acid.

38:57.000 --> 39:01.000
Acid rain can destroy forests.

39:02.000 --> 39:05.000
Our plants and wildlife are in danger too.

39:05.000 --> 39:13.000
Trees give us the oxygen we breathe, but people do not always respect our forests or wildlife.

39:13.000 --> 39:18.000
People cut down many trees every year to make paper and other things.

39:18.000 --> 39:22.000
When we use pesticides, they go into the soil.

39:22.000 --> 39:28.000
This is dangerous because we eat foods from soil.

39:28.000 --> 39:32.000
Fires can also destroy plants and wildlife.

39:32.000 --> 39:36.000
Some people are careless and create fires.

39:36.000 --> 39:40.000
Sometimes these fires burn for several days.

39:40.000 --> 39:45.000
They destroy trees and kill a lot of animals and birds.

39:45.000 --> 39:49.000
So if we want to help conserve our natural resources,

39:49.000 --> 39:53.000
we must be careful and look after the environment.

39:53.000 --> 39:56.000
We must not use too much water.

39:56.000 --> 40:00.000
When we are outside, we must not drop things in the street

40:00.000 --> 40:04.000
or throw things in rivers or in the sea.

40:04.000 --> 40:11.000
Remember, we can help conserve our natural resources only when we work together.

40:11.000 --> 40:17.000
On Saturday morning, Jim, Brian and Susan went to Chinatown police station.

40:17.000 --> 40:24.000
Good afternoon, Brian said to the policeman at the door.

40:25.000 --> 40:30.000
On Saturday morning, Jim, Brian and Susan went to Chinatown police station.

40:30.000 --> 40:34.000
Good afternoon, Brian said to the policeman at the door.

40:34.000 --> 40:36.000
What can I do for you?

40:36.000 --> 40:37.000
Ask the policeman.

40:37.000 --> 40:45.000
We want to report something.

40:45.000 --> 40:46.000
Said Brian.

40:46.000 --> 40:48.000
Come to my office and sit down.

40:48.000 --> 40:49.000
Said the policeman.

40:49.000 --> 40:51.000
I'm Sergeant Chan.

40:51.000 --> 40:54.000
They explained everything to Sergeant Chan.

40:54.000 --> 40:57.000
He was interested and a little surprised.

40:57.000 --> 40:59.000
Why were you at the Stewart Mansion?

40:59.000 --> 41:01.000
Ask Sergeant Chan.

41:01.000 --> 41:04.000
One day, I saw the face of a little girl at the window.

41:04.000 --> 41:05.000
Said Jim.

41:05.000 --> 41:08.000
I told my friends and we wanted to explore it.

41:08.000 --> 41:11.000
Did you see anyone inside this secret lab?

41:11.000 --> 41:12.000
Ask Sergeant Chan.

41:12.000 --> 41:14.000
No, we didn't.

41:14.000 --> 41:15.000
Said Jim.

41:15.000 --> 41:16.000
I understand.

41:16.000 --> 41:18.000
Said Sergeant Chan.

41:18.000 --> 41:21.000
The mansion is very close to Washington Square.

41:21.000 --> 41:24.000
Perhaps you discovered something interesting that night.

41:24.000 --> 41:27.000
I'll send some officers to investigate.

41:27.000 --> 41:29.000
I want you to come too.

41:29.000 --> 41:32.000
You know where the laboratory is.

41:32.000 --> 41:34.000
I'll phone you.

41:34.000 --> 41:35.000
Yes, Sergeant.

41:35.000 --> 41:36.000
Answer Jim.

41:36.000 --> 41:41.000
In the afternoon, the phone rang at Jim's house.

41:41.000 --> 41:42.000
Hello.

41:42.000 --> 41:45.000
This is Sergeant Chan of the San Francisco Police Department.

41:45.000 --> 41:47.000
May I speak to Jim Riley?

41:47.000 --> 41:48.000
This is Jim Riley.

41:48.000 --> 41:50.000
Hello, Sergeant Chan.

41:50.000 --> 41:54.000
Jim, my officers and I are going to investigate the Stewart Mansion.

41:54.000 --> 41:57.000
Can we meet you at five o'clock this afternoon?

41:57.000 --> 41:58.000
Of course.

41:58.000 --> 42:02.000
Let's meet in front of my house at 325 Lombard Street.

42:02.000 --> 42:03.000
Then we can go together.

42:03.000 --> 42:04.000
Said Jim.

42:04.000 --> 42:07.000
You and your friends wait outside your house.

42:07.000 --> 42:09.000
We'll go in a police car.

42:09.000 --> 42:10.000
Said Sergeant Chan.

42:10.000 --> 42:12.000
We'll see you at five o'clock then.

42:12.000 --> 42:14.000
Goodbye.

42:14.000 --> 42:15.000
Jim was excited.

42:15.000 --> 42:18.000
He told his grandfather about the phone call.

42:18.000 --> 42:21.000
I'm very proud of you and your friends.

42:21.000 --> 42:23.000
You're doing the right thing.

42:23.000 --> 42:25.000
Said his grandfather.

42:25.000 --> 42:28.000
He smiled, but he was worried.

42:28.000 --> 42:30.000
Thanks, Grandpa.

42:30.000 --> 42:33.000
Jim called Brian and Susan.

42:33.000 --> 42:35.000
Meet me outside my house.

42:35.000 --> 42:38.000
The police are going to drive us to the mansion.

42:38.000 --> 42:40.000
It was five p.m.

42:40.000 --> 42:43.000
Jim saw two police cars in front of his house.

42:43.000 --> 42:47.000
He and his friends got into the police car with Sergeant Chan.

42:47.000 --> 42:48.000
Good evening.

42:48.000 --> 42:49.000
This is Sergeant Lopez.

42:49.000 --> 42:51.000
Said Sergeant Chan.

42:51.000 --> 42:52.000
Please meet me, sir.

42:52.000 --> 42:54.000
Said Jim Brian and Susan.

42:54.000 --> 42:56.000
Now this is our plan.

42:56.000 --> 43:01.000
We'll drive to the mansion and my officers and I will go in.

43:01.000 --> 43:05.000
Jim, you will show us the basement window.

43:05.000 --> 43:08.000
After that, you must stay outside the mansion.

43:08.000 --> 43:12.000
Only the police will enter because it can be dangerous.

43:12.000 --> 43:13.000
Do you understand?

43:13.000 --> 43:14.000
Yes, I do, sir.

43:14.000 --> 43:16.000
I'll wait outside with my friends.

43:16.000 --> 43:18.000
Said Jim.

43:18.000 --> 43:21.000
The police car drove up Telegraph Hill.

43:21.000 --> 43:28.000
When they arrived in front of the Stewart Mansion, Jim, Sergeant Chan and Sergeant Lopez got out of the car.

43:28.000 --> 43:31.000
Three policemen got out of the second car.

43:31.000 --> 43:34.000
The five men followed Jim.

43:34.000 --> 43:37.000
He took them to the gate.

43:37.000 --> 43:40.000
The policeman looked around.

43:40.000 --> 43:44.000
You go around the back of the house and we'll go around the front.

43:44.000 --> 43:46.000
Said Sergeant Chan to the other policeman.

43:46.000 --> 43:49.000
Where did you see this laboratory?

43:49.000 --> 43:50.000
Sergeant Chan asked Jim.

43:50.000 --> 43:54.000
Over there, by the window, replied Jim.

43:54.000 --> 43:57.000
They saw yellow smoke near the basement window.

43:57.000 --> 44:00.000
It was a bad smell like before.

44:00.000 --> 44:02.000
That's the smell of sulfur.

44:02.000 --> 44:03.000
Said Sergeant Chan.

44:03.000 --> 44:05.000
And it's very strong.

44:05.000 --> 44:08.000
He opened the gate and went in.

44:08.000 --> 44:10.000
The other policeman followed him.

44:10.000 --> 44:15.000
Jim remained outside with his friends and waited.

44:23.000 --> 44:26.000
Chapter 8. The Secret Formula

44:27.000 --> 44:37.000
There were four young people in the laboratory, two women and two men.

44:37.000 --> 44:42.000
They were in their early twenties and they were very busy with an experiment.

44:42.000 --> 44:45.000
They stood around the long table.

44:45.000 --> 44:48.000
One woman wrote something in the big black book.

44:48.000 --> 44:52.000
The other three worked with the test tubes.

44:52.000 --> 44:55.000
There was a portable computer on a small desk.

44:55.000 --> 44:58.000
Near the desk, there was a little girl.

44:58.000 --> 45:04.000
The little girl was with the man with long hair and a silver earring.

45:04.000 --> 45:10.000
Sergeant Chan looked inside the basement window and saw people in the laboratory.

45:10.000 --> 45:12.000
Jim Riley was right.

45:12.000 --> 45:14.000
There is an illegal laboratory here.

45:14.000 --> 45:15.000
Let's go in.

45:15.000 --> 45:17.000
Said Sergeant Chan to his men.

45:17.000 --> 45:21.000
The police broke the front door and went into the mansion.

45:21.000 --> 45:24.000
They immediately went to the basement.

45:24.000 --> 45:26.000
This is the San Francisco Police Department.

45:26.000 --> 45:28.000
Put your hands over your heads.

45:28.000 --> 45:30.000
Sergeant Lopez cried.

45:30.000 --> 45:31.000
You have the right to remain silent.

45:31.000 --> 45:34.000
Anything you say can be used against you.

45:34.000 --> 45:36.000
The young people were surprised and angry.

45:36.000 --> 45:37.000
Oh no!

45:37.000 --> 45:39.000
cried one young man.

45:39.000 --> 45:43.000
He and his friend ran to another door, but the police stopped them.

45:43.000 --> 45:46.000
Who are you and what are you doing here?

45:46.000 --> 45:48.000
Do you know you're on private property?

45:48.000 --> 45:50.000
Said Sergeant Chan.

45:50.000 --> 45:52.000
One of the young women spoke.

45:52.000 --> 45:54.000
She was very nervous.

45:54.000 --> 45:56.000
My name is Barbara Dell.

45:56.000 --> 45:58.000
We aren't criminals.

45:58.000 --> 46:03.000
We're students at San Francisco University in the Department of Chemistry.

46:03.000 --> 46:04.000
Who is that man?

46:04.000 --> 46:06.000
He doesn't look like a student.

46:06.000 --> 46:07.000
Said Sergeant Chan.

46:07.000 --> 46:09.000
He's Ben Bradley.

46:09.000 --> 46:15.000
He has the key to the mansion because his grandfather was a gardener here many years ago.

46:15.000 --> 46:17.000
Now Ben doesn't have a home.

46:17.000 --> 46:19.000
He sleeps here at night.

46:19.000 --> 46:21.000
Said Barbara Dell.

46:21.000 --> 46:22.000
Aw shut up.

46:22.000 --> 46:24.000
Said Ben Bradley angrily.

46:24.000 --> 46:25.000
Be quiet.

46:25.000 --> 46:27.000
Said Sergeant Chan.

46:27.000 --> 46:29.000
Now continue your story.

46:29.000 --> 46:31.000
Don't tell them anything Barbara.

46:31.000 --> 46:33.000
Cried one of the young men.

46:33.000 --> 46:35.000
The formula is our secret.

46:35.000 --> 46:36.000
I want to tell the truth.

46:36.000 --> 46:38.000
Said Barbara.

46:38.000 --> 46:41.000
We discovered a new molecule at the university.

46:41.000 --> 46:47.000
With this molecule, we created a new formula for a powerful fertilizer.

46:47.000 --> 46:50.000
People can use this fertilizer without water.

46:50.000 --> 46:53.000
We knew that no one lived in this mansion.

46:53.000 --> 46:59.000
And we knew that there was an old laboratory in the basement because Mr. Stewart was a scientist.

46:59.000 --> 47:02.000
We wanted to keep this a secret because-

47:02.000 --> 47:05.000
Because you wanted to sell it to a company and make a lot of money.

47:05.000 --> 47:08.000
And you tested the fertilizer in Washington Square.

47:08.000 --> 47:11.000
You polluted the water of the duck pond.

47:11.000 --> 47:14.000
You killed the ducks and the fish.

47:14.000 --> 47:18.000
Your new fertilizer is toxic and very dangerous.

47:18.000 --> 47:21.000
Do you know the children play in the park near the duck pond?

47:21.000 --> 47:23.000
Ask Sergeant Chan angrily.

47:23.000 --> 47:27.000
We didn't want to pollute the water in the pond or the grass in the park.

47:27.000 --> 47:29.000
Said one of the young men.

47:29.000 --> 47:31.000
We just wanted to test the new fertilizer.

47:31.000 --> 47:35.000
And you decided to test it in a public park.

47:35.000 --> 47:38.000
Didn't you think about the people and the wildlife?

47:38.000 --> 47:40.000
You four must come with us to the police station.

47:40.000 --> 47:42.000
Said Sergeant Chan.

47:42.000 --> 47:46.000
We will also take all the chemicals you're using in this laboratory.

47:46.000 --> 47:47.000
Sorry.

47:47.000 --> 47:51.000
The little girl at the desk was scared and started crying.

47:51.000 --> 47:55.000
She ran to Barbara Dell.

47:55.000 --> 47:56.000
Who is she?

47:56.000 --> 47:57.000
Ask Sergeant Lopez.

47:57.000 --> 47:59.000
She's my little sister.

47:59.000 --> 48:01.000
I bring her here sometimes.

48:01.000 --> 48:03.000
Said Barbara.

48:03.000 --> 48:08.000
Then the policeman, the university students, and Ben Bradley came out of the mansion.

48:08.000 --> 48:12.000
Jim, Brian, and Susan were outside.

48:12.000 --> 48:15.000
When Jim saw Ben Bradley, he was very surprised.

48:15.000 --> 48:17.000
It's the man from the supermarket.

48:17.000 --> 48:19.000
He thought.

48:19.000 --> 48:21.000
The little girl looked at Jim.

48:21.000 --> 48:23.000
Well, she's not a ghost.

48:23.000 --> 48:24.000
She's real.

48:24.000 --> 48:26.000
He thought.

48:26.000 --> 48:30.000
Sergeant Chan smiled at Jim, Brian, and Susan and said,

48:30.000 --> 48:33.000
You helped us a lot. Thank you.

48:33.000 --> 48:37.000
Come to the police station tomorrow and I'll explain everything.

48:37.000 --> 48:39.000
Thank you again.

48:39.000 --> 48:43.000
The police cars drove away.

48:43.000 --> 48:47.000
The next day, the three friends went to talk to Sergeant Chan.

48:47.000 --> 48:50.000
Those university students were very intelligent.

48:50.000 --> 48:51.000
Said Jim.

48:51.000 --> 48:53.000
They created a new formula.

48:53.000 --> 48:56.000
Yes, but they were also very irresponsible.

48:56.000 --> 49:00.000
We found many illegal chemicals in that basement.

49:00.000 --> 49:03.000
Those chemicals are very toxic.

49:03.000 --> 49:06.000
Now we must close Washington Square for a few weeks.

49:06.000 --> 49:11.000
There will be a lot of work for our chemical experts, said Sergeant Chan.

49:11.000 --> 49:14.000
What will happen to the university students?

49:14.000 --> 49:15.000
Ask Susan.

49:15.000 --> 49:18.000
There will be a trial, said Sergeant Chan.

49:18.000 --> 49:20.000
They could go to prison.

49:20.000 --> 49:21.000
How are the other ducks?

49:21.000 --> 49:22.000
Ask Brian.

49:22.000 --> 49:25.000
The volunteers at helping hands are looking after them.

49:25.000 --> 49:29.000
They're feeling better, said Sergeant Chan.

49:29.000 --> 49:32.000
Jim, Brian, and Susan left the police station.

49:32.000 --> 49:34.000
They were all happy.

49:34.000 --> 49:37.000
Pizza for everyone tonight, said Jim.

49:37.000 --> 49:39.000
Great idea, said Brian.

49:39.000 --> 49:42.000
Let's go to Nico's pizza place on Washington Square.

49:42.000 --> 49:43.000
Said Susan.

49:43.000 --> 49:46.000
Jim and Brian looked worried.

49:46.000 --> 49:47.000
Don't worry.

49:47.000 --> 49:49.000
I'm only joking.

49:49.000 --> 49:51.000
Said Susan laughing.

50:09.000 --> 50:15.000
MUSIC

